---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { publicSiteUrl } from "../lib/public-url";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Changelog | ComplyEaze Tools"
  description="Public changelog for ComplyEaze Tools releases, trust-surface improvements, source-register updates, and static deployment changes."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <h1>Changelog.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Public release notes for source-backed local tools, trust-surface
        changes, and static deployment updates.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="detail-grid" aria-label="Release notes">
    <article>
      <h2>2026-07-03: artifact trust references</h2>
      <p>
        Added a public Terms and Disclaimer page, linked tool outputs to privacy,
        source, terms, and repository references, and expanded downloaded draft
        metadata with local artifact IDs, page URLs, detected input shape, and
        row diagnostics.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href={publicSiteUrl("/terms")}>Read terms and disclaimer</a>
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>2026-07-03: review-copy safety hardening</h2>
      <p>
        Broadened Review Copy Builder masking checks and added found, checked,
        not-checked, and manual-review sections so the output is clear about
        what was and was not automatically reviewed.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href={publicSiteUrl("/privacy/review-copy-builder")}>Open Review Copy Builder</a>
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>2026-07-03: browser-local tool depth</h2>
      <p>
        Expanded the launch tools with richer MSME payables triage, supplier
        follow-ups, GSTR-2B reconciliation buckets, AIS/Form 26AS review drafts,
        GST portal evidence memos, parser diagnostics, source-backed SEO
        sections, and Axal upgrade paths.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href={publicSiteUrl("/")}>Browse the tools</a>
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>2026-07-03: initial static launch posture</h2>
      <p>
        Shipped source-backed landing pages, browser-local workbench
        foundations, policy tests, open-source governance files, and static
        Kubernetes deployment manifests.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
